oi: 10.1016/j.bbrc.2005.10.186.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType=\"doi\">10.1016/j.bbrc.2005.10.186</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">16293225</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Pfeffer M., Gispert S., Auburger G., Wicht H., Korf H.W. Impact of Ataxin-2 knock out on circadian locomotor behavior and PER immunoreaction in the SCN of mice. Chronobiol. Int. 2017;34:129&#x2013;137. doi: 10.1080/07420528.2016.1245666.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType=\"doi\">10.1080/07420528.2016.1245666</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">27791392</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Kiehl T.R., Shibata H., Pulst S.M. The ortholog of human ataxin-2 is essential for early embryonic patterning in C. elegans. J. Mol. Neurosci. 2000;15:231&#x2013;241. doi: 10.1385/JMN:15:3:231.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType=\"doi\">10.1385/JMN:15:3:231</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">11303786</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Gadgil A., Raczynska K.D. U7 snRNA: A tool for gene therapy. J. Gene Med. 2021;23:e3321. doi: 10.1002/jgm.3321.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType=\"doi\">10.1002/jgm.3321</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType=\"pmc\">PMC8243935</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">33590603</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Liu J.L., Gall J.G. U bodies are cytoplasmic structures that contain uridine-rich small nuclear ribonucleoproteins and associate with P bodies. Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. USA. 2007;104:11655&#x2013;11659. doi: 10.1073/pnas.0704977104.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType=\"doi\">10.1073/pnas.0704977104</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType=\"pmc\">PMC1899408</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">17595295</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Jacobs E.Y., Frey M.R., Wu W., Ingledue T.C., Gebuhr T.C., Gao L., Marzluff W.F., Matera A.G. Coiled bodies preferentially associate with U4, U11, and U12 small nuclear RNA genes